## Equipment
Equipment is defined via a fluent class with methods:
- `.preheat(temp)` → timer step "Preheat X to Y°", 15 minutes
- `.cook(label, duration, temperature?)` → timer step
- `.add(ingredients[], note?)` → container step with one child per ingredient
- `.stir()` / `.mix()` → instruction steps

Available equipment: bowl, pan, pot, oven, toaster oven, instant pot, bullet mixer, knife, cutting board.

---

## Ingredients
Ingredient factory functions `(quantity, unit) => Ingredient`. Optional metadata:
- `purchaseLinks` — nested by store → variant → array of `{ price, quantity, quantityUnit, link, organic?, discount? }`
- `nutrition` — keyed by unit name, with fields for servings, calories, sodium, sugar, protein
- `perishableDays`, `isMeatProduct`

Simple ingredients with no metadata are declared via a bulk `simpleIngredients()` helper that auto-derives display names from camelCase keys.

---

## Units
Supported: none, cup, tbsp, tsp, ounce, pound, fl oz, unit, handful, spray, bag.

Quantities are formatted with unicode fractions (¼, ½, ¾, etc.) where applicable.

---

## Time Helpers
`time.seconds(n)`, `time.minutes(n)`, `time.hours(n)` — all return a number of seconds.

`Timer.set(amount, unit, label)` and `Timer.end()` allow inline timer steps without equipment context.

---

## Stores
Named constants for Amazon, Amazon Fresh, Whole Foods — used as keys in purchase link objects.

---

## Styling
Dark theme (#111 background, #f0f0f0 text). Large touch-friendly cards (font-size 22px, padding 20px). All styles are injected as a `<style>` tag at bootstrap time — no external CSS file.

Key visual states:
- Selected recipe: green background
- Starred recipe: gold star
- Active timer: amber/yellow card
- Completed timer: green card with ✓ and timestamp
- Skipped timer: grey card with strikethrough and timestamp
- Locked step: 45% opacity, red left border, "⏳ waiting…" pill
- Unlock flash: brief green border/background animation
- Recipe title on cooking screen: name followed by `estimated X min · actual Xm XXs` badge in muted colour, actual time updating every second and freezing when all steps are done

---

## Audio
A beep sound plays when a timer completes. The audio element is unlocked on first user tap (browser autoplay policy workaround).

---

## Bootstrap
The app mounts on `DOMContentLoaded`, injects styles, renders `<div id="app">`, and calls `render()`. All state lives in a single `state` object. No persistence between page loads.